air-pilih-bandara-adi-sumarmo-ketimbang-yia</ref><ref>https://www.suaramerdeka.com/amp/news/baca/214694/xpressair-buka-rute-baru-dari-jateng-ke-kalimantan-dan-sumatera</ref>}}\n\n==Statistics and traffic==\n===Traffic===\n{{Bar chart\n| title       = '''Overall Operational Statistics'''<ref name=\"dephub\">{{cite web|url=http://hubud.dephub.go.id/?id/llu/index/filter:category,0|title=Lalu Lintas Angkutan Udara Bandara Internasional Supadio|author=Indonesian Minsitry of Transportation|accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref>\n| bar_width   = 19\n| width_units = em\n| label_type  =Year\n| label1  = 2002\n| label2  = 2003\n| label3  = 2004\n| label4  = 2005\n| label5  = 2006\n| label6  = 2007\n| label7  = 2008\n| label8  = 2009\n| label9  = 2010\n| label10  =2011\n| label11 = 2012\n| label12 = 2013\n| label13 = 2014\n| label14 = 2015\n| label15 = 2016\n| data_type = Passengers movements\n| data_max  = 3923988\n| data1  = 597,688\n| data2  = 835,546\n| data3  = 1,085,019\n| data4  = 1,124,225\n| data5  = 1,220,592\n| data6  = 1,378,529\n| data7  = 1,390,622\n| data8  = 1,581,931\n| data9  = 1,186,170\n| data10 = \n| data11 = 2,291,470\n| data12 = 2,307,322\n| data13 = 2,502,957\n| data14 = 2,713,259\n| data15 = 3,182,267\n| col2_data_type = Aircraft movements\n| col2_data_max  = 45755\n| col2_data1  = 16,113\n| col2_data2  = 19,196\n| col2_data3  = 21,186\n| col2_data4  = 20,151\n| col2_data5  = 17,591\n| col2_data6  = 17,898\n| col2_data7  = 17,461\n| col2_data8  = 9,440\n| col2_data9  = 11,135\n| col2_data10 = \n| col2_data11 = 21,198\n| col2_data12 = 22,779\n| col2_data13 = 23,626\n| col2_data14 = 25,184\n| col2_data15 = 28,732\n| col3_data_type = Freight movements\n| col3_data_max  = 100000\n| col3_data1  = 3,993\n| col3_data2  = 5,155\n| col3_data3  = 5,874\n| col3_data4  = 7,005 \n| col3_data5  = 7,726\n| col3_data6  = 9,017\n| col3_data7  = 9,227\n| col3_data8  = 12,400\n| col3_data9  = 6,904\n| col3_data10 = \n| col3_data11 = 26,518\n| col3_data12 = 7,729\n| col3_data13 = 17,305\n| col3_data14 = 15,368\n| col3_data15 = 16,399\n}}\n\n===Statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:89%;\" cellpadding=4\n|+ The Frequency of Domestic Flights at Supadio International Airport\n|- \n! |Rank|| |Destinations|| |Frequency (Weekly)|| Airline(s)\n|-\n|1\n|[[Soekarno Hatta International Airport|Jakarta Soekarno-Hatta]], Special Capital Region\n|189\n|Citilink, Garuda Indonesia, Lion Air, NAM Air, Sriwijaya Air\n|-\n|2\n|[[Ketapang Airport|Ketapang]], West Kalimantan\n|70\n|Citilink, NAM Air, Wings Air\n|-\n|3\n|[[Pangsuma Airport|Putussibau]], West Kalimantan\n|21\n|Citilink, NAM Air, Wings Air\n|-\n|4\n|[[Tebelian Airport|Sintang]], West Kalimantan\n|21\n|NAM Air, Wings Air\n|-\n|5\n|[[Juanda International Airport|Surabaya]], East Java\n|21\n|Citilink, Lion Air, Wings Air\n|-\n|6\n|[[Hang Nadim International Airport|Batam]], Riau Islands\n|21\n|Citilink, Lion Air\n|-\n|7\n|[[Syamsudin Noor International Airport|Banjarmasin]], South Kalimantan\n|14\n|NAM Air\n|-\n|8\n|[[Achmad Yani International Airport|Semarang]], Central Java\n|7\n|Lion Air\n|-\n|9\n|[[Yogyakarta International Airport|Yogyakarta-International]], Yogyakarta Special Region\n|7\n|Lion Air\n|- \n|10\n|[[Sultan Hasanuddin International Airport|Makassar]], South Sulawesi\n|7\n|Lion Air\n|-\n|11\n|[[Sultan Aji Muhammad Sulaiman Airport|Balikpapan]], East Kalimantan\n|4\n|Lion Air\n|-\n|12\n|[[Adisumarmo International Airport|Surakarta/Solo]], Central Java\n|4\n|NAM Air, Xpress Air\n|-\n|13\n|[[Tjilik Riwut Airport|Palangkaraya]], Central Kalimantan\n|1\n|Wings Air\n|-\n|}\n<br>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:89%;\" cellpadding=4\n|+ The Frequency of International Flights at Supadio International Airport\n|- \n! |Rank|| |Destinations|| |Frequency (Weekly)|| Airline(s)\n|-\n|1\n|{{flagicon|Malaysia}} [[Kuching International Airport|Kuching]], Malaysia\n|14\n|AirAsia, Wings Air\n|-\n|2\n|{{flagicon|Malaysia}} [[Kuala Lumpur International Airport|Kuala Lumpur\u2013International]], Malaysia\n|7\n|AirAsia, Indonesia AirAsia\n|}{{clear left}}\n\n==Expansion==\nSupadio International Airport is going to have new terminal building with its runway to be lengthened and widened, to make it a world-class airport. In 2012 tender to overlay 2,250 meters runway has been done, and in early 2013 overlay will be done. Multiyears project to expand runway to 2,500 meters began in 2013. Before, in 2010\u20132011 runway has been widened from 30 meters to 45 meters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://industri.kontan.co.id/news/angkasa-pura-ii-segera-perluas-bandara-supadio/2013/01/03 |title=Angkasa Pura II segera perluas bandara Supadio |date=3 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe new terminal was now being constructed and expected to be finished totally by 2016. The project would be separated into 2 phase. Phase I involves building a temporary terminal with an area of 13.000 m2 and could accommodate over 1.5&nbsp;million people over a year. This temporary building would be located adjacent to the existing terminal, Phase 2 involves demolishing of existing terminal building and building a new terminal building as an extension of the building in phase I. In total, the new Supadio Airport terminal would have an area of 32.000 m2 and could accommodate 2.5&nbsp;million people a year.<ref>http://bisnis.news.viva.co.id/news/read/556851-bangun-terminal-baru-bandara-supadio--angkasa-pura-ii-rogoh-rp370-m</ref>\n\n==Military use==\nSupadio International Airport is also used by Aviation Squadron 51 (Skadron Udara 51), which operates the [[CAIG Wing Loong]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.janes.com/article/78147/indonesia-acquires-four-wing-loong-i-uavs-from-china |title=Indonesia acquires four Wing Loong I UAVs from China |first=Ridzwan |last=Rahmat |date=25 February 2018 |publisher=[[Jane's Information Group]] |quote=Aviation Squadron 51 is based near the city of Pontianak in West Kalimantan, and the unit shares a runway with the Supadio International Airport.}}</ref>\n\n==Accidents and incidents==\n* On 19 January 1973, [[Douglas DC-3|Douglas C-47B]] PK-EHC of [[Trans Nusantara Airways]] crashed on landing and was destroyed in the subsequent fire. All four people on board escaped.<ref name=ASN190173>{{cite web|url=http://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=19730119-1 |title=PK-EHC Accident description |publisher=Aviation Safety Network |accessdate=26 August 2010}}</ref>\n* On 22 November 2004, Sri Hardono, the captain of [[Garuda Indonesia]] flight 501, a [[Boeing 737 Classic|Boeing 737-500]] from Pontianak to Jakarta, was suddenly ill shortly after take-off. Hardono immediately asked permission to the air traffic control to return to the airport. Hardono died shortly after the emergency landing while still in the cockpit. Heart attack was the cause of illness and death. Due to the incident, the airport was temporarily closed for 40 minutes. There were no other injuries or fatalities in this incident.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070311203836/http://www.tempointeraktif.com/hg/nusa/kalimantan/2004/11/22/brk,20041122-60,id.html Tempo Interaktif Pilot Garuda Diduga Meninggal Karena Serangan Jantung]</ref>\n* On 2 November 2010, [[Lion Air]] flight 712, operated by [[Boeing 737 Classic|Boeing 737-400]] PK-LIQ, overran the runway on landing, coming to rest on its belly. All 174 passengers and crew evacuated by the [[evacuation slide|emergency chutes]], with few injuries reported.<ref name=AH432fa0b7>{{cite web|url=http://avherald.com/h?article=432fa0b7&opt=0 |title=Accident: Lionair B734 at Pontianak on Nov 2nd 2010, overran runway on landing |publisher=Aviation Herald |first=Simon |last=Hradecky |accessdate=2 November 2010}}</ref>\n* On 1 June 2012, a Sriwijaya Air [[Boeing 737 Classic|Boeing 737-400]] skidded off the runway in heavy rain. Nobody was hurt, but the plane sustained damage beyond repair.<ref>http://www.couriermail.com.au/ipad/passenger-plane-skids-off-runway/story-fn6ck55c-1226381089076</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thejakartaglobe.com/news/indonesian-airliner-carrying-163-skids-off-runway-none-hurt/521605 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-06-02 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120603234821/http://www.thejakartaglobe.com/news/indonesian-airliner-carrying-163-skids-off-runway-none-hurt/521605 |archivedate=3 June 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Supadio Airport}}\n* {{ASN|PNK}}\n{{Airports in Indonesia}}\n\n[[Category:Airports in West Kalimantan]]\n", "name_user": "Meandkancil2020", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePassenger:Indonesia AirAsia (QZ) , Suspension Period Exact Ends Date , With A Valid Reference .", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supadio_International_Airport"}
